<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_fe6006fd-6416-4943-921c-69010693f2dd" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="TAS"><sptc>C4P1</sptc><title id="_c6062032-d2fa-4684-a058-818c28f0fe63">Health, environment and amenity protection</title><archive-num>2019: Tas HP2.1</archive-num><subclause id="_fa8520d5-4d0e-412c-bd36-6cbed3b87f9a" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_1cb2d1ac-8f40-40c3-9461-251064d04c9a">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>An on-site liquid trade waste system must ensure—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_98fa8d62-1567-48b5-8349-e51d7f659026">the risks associated with the discharge of treated liquid trade waste to the environment are minimised; and</li><li id="_03f3e8c3-89e3-4f84-9144-2041d3f834d4"><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1486_26.7.0.xml#_02c3900f-c9bb-470b-93f4-d71555f2fea7" id="_3e11c63f-fef5-4c65-8c97-e54149e794cf" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">surface water</xref> and ground water are not polluted; and</li><li id="_f6e2e068-15f8-4b4a-90fc-74f380271506">soil productivity is maintained or enhanced.</li></ol></subclause></clause>